This recipe is definitely a keeper with my friends and family. The final result was surprisingly balanced. Although the use of cherry cola would make some worry the recipe to be too sweet, this is not at all so. The dijon mustard with horseradish gives these ribs a perfect ying-yang bang for your dollar!! One definite suggestion would be if using cherry preserves, to strain the final product through a chinoix or conical sieve. This seperates the seed and pulp and produces a smooth, velvety glaze. Try this one time and you'll be hooked.

