Rating: 4
When I saw the cover recipe for the July issue of Bon Appetit - I knew I'd found the perfect dish for our annual 4th of July party at our cottage on the lake. The recipe surpassed all expectations! Each of my guests asked for the recipe and all enthusiastically said that they were the best ribs they'd ever had! The recipe is great for entertaining as everything can be prepared in advance. The recipe is very easy - I followed it exactly. Making the sauce is time consuming because of the waiting period for the cola to flatten; the reducing period for the cola; and the final reduction of the sauce (next time around, I'll simply let the cola flatten overnight) However, since this can be made ahead of time - this remains a wonderful recipe for entertaining! Baking the ribs in advance made the final grilling process a breeze. No one at our party had every baked ribs as directed in the recipe (individually wrapped in foil and slow roasted)- but the end result was so outstanding, I think this is the only way we'll be cooking ribs from now on!

