this was one of the best rib recipes i have tried. you do need to start this in advance due to the cherry cola needing to "de-fizz" and for the sauce to cook for awhile. i would make more sauce than the recipe calls for..but it was very tasty. i par-boil my ribs in a big pot of water for an hour or until tender. then i place them on heavy aluminum foil..baste with the marinade, wrap the foil, and put them on the grill for 15 minutes to get hot. for the last 5 minutes, i place the ribs directly on the grill, turning once, just to crisp the up a tad. a great recipe!!!!!!!!!!!!!!